NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|2S was the correct bid Sandy. Just to explain further why 2S was correct. In general, when you have a weak hand with a long suit, it is better to play in the weak hand's long suit. The reason is, if you play in the long suit, the low cards in that suit will take tricks. Whereas if you play in another suit, they often will not.|
PG| ***** 78 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Even on that hand, where we had a 7-card diamond fit, we do at least as well in our 6-card spade fit. BTW, 2S over 1N is to play. If sandy had an invitational or better hand, she would have bid NMF (2C).|
